and, in an amount determined annually by the department of military's policy,
undergraduate course fees or master's degree program fees charged by the educational
institution attended for the educational program to which the member successfully
applied, less all other state or federal financial assistance as described in ยง 49-4-1005.
Such financial assistance must be credited first to the member's tuition, subject to ยง 49-
4-1005. The department of military shall publish the policy establishing the payment
amounts for undergraduate course fees and master's degree program fees pursuant to
this subsection (b) on the department of military's website by August 1 each year for the
upcoming academic year.
